    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-23T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-23T19:00:00-05:00" n="428"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d428">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Pacific War/1383: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Australia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canberra</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-24T10:00:00+10:00"
                            >December 24, 1941—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:21 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>92. Ministry External Affairs has shown me appeal made yesterday by Prime
                    Minister to President and Churchill<note n="83" xml:id="d428fn1">See <hi
                            rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note> and asked me to support it. I do most
                    earnestly support Curtin’s statement of the situation. People in the Pacific
                    area await news of definite movement to stop Japanese advances which if
                    permitted to continue threaten to deprive us of every advantage.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
